\b Codex 13 Student Dev Kit - terms and privacy\b0\par
\par
The installer prepares a portable Codex 13 development environment on this computer. Before installation, accept:\par
\par
\b 1. Project terms and licenses.\b0\par
Codex 13 Student Dev Kit is provided under the project license. Third-party components, including Visual Studio Code, Git for Windows, OpenSSH and XAMPP, remain subject to their own license terms.\par
\par
\b 2. Downloading and configuring components.\b0\par
The installer may download, verify, unpack and configure third-party tools according to the selected profile and preset.\par
\par
\b 3. Privacy and local logs.\b0\par
The installer does not require registration and does not send personal data to Luczak Consulting P.S.A. or Naster Labs. Installation logs are stored locally and may include file paths, component versions, download URLs, verification results and error messages.\par
\par
Full legal and license texts will be written to the legal and licenses directories inside the installation directory.\par
